div.p:
                  THe Presbyterial Government has Four
Iudicatories. A Parochial Session;
A Presbyterial Consistory; A Provincial Synode;
And A General Assembly.

From the Triple-Crown'd Consistory;
that Lords it over Souls, Bodies, and Estates;
over Kings, Nobles, and Commons;
over Laws, Magistrates, and all Sorts, and
Ranks of Men, and Interests; That Turns
Gospel into Law; Communities into Deserts;
Men into Beasts;
